\dfrac{p}{p+3}=\dfrac{2p-1}{2p}
p
\frac{p}{p+3}=\frac{2p-1}{2p}
p\neq 0
p+3\neq 0\implies p\neq -3
\begin{align*} p\cdot 2p&=(2p-1)(p+3)\\ 2p^2&=(2p-1)(p+3)\\ 2p^2&=2p^2-p+6p-3\\ 2p^2&=2p^2+5p-3\\ 2p^2-2p^2&=5p-3\\ 3&=5p\\ p&=\frac{3}{5} \end{align*}
\frac{p}{p+3}=\frac{2p-1}{2p}\Rightarrow 1-\frac{p}{p+3}=1-\frac{2p-1}{2p}\Rightarrow \frac{3}{p+3}=\frac{1}{2p}\Rightarrow 6p=p+3\Rightarrow p=\frac{3}{5}
\dfrac {p - (p + 3)} {p + 3} = \dfrac {2p - 1 - (2p)} {2p}
\dfrac {- 3} {p + 3} = \dfrac {- 1} {2p}
6p = p + 3
